1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,500
On April seventh, twenty twenty six, Anthropic disclosed Claude Mythos Preview and Project Glasswing.

2
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:15,000
The important signal is not one model name.

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:22,500
It is that autonomous cyber capability is now credible enough to compress vulnerability discovery, exploitation, and defensive response cycles.

4
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:30,000
Quarry is built for this new clock: machine-speed investigation with human governance.

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:40,000
The analyst starts with a natural-language brief.

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:50,000
In this demo, the case is organized Pix fraud at a fictitious Brazilian fintech called FinPlay Pagamentos.

7
00:00:50,000 --> 00:01:00,000
The brief describes five hundred suspicious transactions in thirty days, with newly created accounts receiving fragmented values and redistributing them to potential mule accounts.

8
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Quarry decomposes the brief into testable hypotheses.

9
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:30,000
It does not jump directly to an answer.

10
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:45,000
It proposes a mule-account ring, a possible SIM-swap origin for a high-value account, anomalous Open Finance access, and a boleto fraud campaign.

11
00:01:45,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Each hypothesis has a confidence score, expected evidence, and the data sources that should be queried.

12
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:12,000
The agent now runs controlled queries.

13
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:24,000
The important product decision is governance. Query execution is visible.

14
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Cost and token usage are visible.

15
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:48,000
Read-only evaluation paths are enforced for benchmark work.

16
00:02:48,000 --> 00:03:00,000
The Investigation Ledger records the questions, the evidence, and the reasoning path so the analyst can challenge or reproduce the result.

17
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:20,000
The system correlates events into findings.

18
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Here, the suspicious flow crosses twenty newly created accounts, ninety-six thousand Pix events, and more than two hundred fifty thousand reais in correlated value.

19
00:03:40,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Instead of a black-box answer, the analyst receives prioritized findings, related entities, and a graph that explains why the case deserves attention.

20
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:10,000
Quarry then generates an analyst-ready report. The report is not just prose.

21
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:20,000
It is backed by the ledger: hypotheses, queries, findings, timeline, MITRE context where relevant, and a defensible conclusion.

22
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:30,000
This is the output a security leader can review, improve, and send forward.

23
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:37,500
The final reveal is cost and time.

24
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:45,000
In the demo, Quarry shows machine cost next to an estimated human analyst cost and hours saved.

25
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:52,500
The claim is not that humans disappear.

26
00:04:52,500 --> 00:05:00,000
The claim is that senior investigation capacity becomes measurable, repeatable, and dramatically faster under human control.
